Synopsis: This function retrieves Group Policy Client Side Extensions (CSEs) from a specified Windows computer.
Description: The Find-CSExtension function lists Group Policy Client Side Extensions (CSEs) configured on a Windows computer. It queries the Windows Registry to retrieve information about the CSEs.

Examples.Title: EXAMPLE 1
Examples.Code:
Find-CSExtension -ComputerName "Computer01"
Retrieves all CSEs configured on the computer named "Computer01".

Examples.Title: EXAMPLE 2
Examples.Code:
Find-CSExtension -CSE "CSE1", "CSE2" -ComputerName "Computer02"
Retrieves information about CSEs named "CSE1" and "CSE2" on the computer named "Computer02".
